Amper Sales to Grow 60% on Elandia Purchase, Expansion Reports

-- B y   S h a r o n   S m y t h
-- 
2011-04-01T06:12:22Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-01/amper-sales-to-grow-60-on-elandia-purchase-expansion-reports.html
Sales at  Amper SA (AMP) , the Spanish maker
of communications equipment, will grow 60 percent this year on
the purchase of an 85 percent stake in U.S.-based Elandia
International Inc.,  Expansion  reported, without citing anyone.  The company expects sales of 420 million euros ($595.3
million) this year, compared with 262 million euros last year,
the newspaper said.  To contact the reporters on this story:
Sharon Smyth in Madrid at 
 ssmyth2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew Blackman at   ablackman@bloomberg.net . 